					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4099042#post-3622017</guid>
				<title>Author&#039;s Note</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4099042/kit-s-horror-hospital-of-horror#post-3622017</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2017 14:32:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zachary Maxwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2975899</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So, I wasn't sure I could post this in time for Halloween, as I have sporadic access to the internet, but I managed it, so huzzah!</p> <p>I hope I didn't bastardise <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-1471">SCP-1471</a> too much, and I hope you enjoy this Tale that turned out more about loneliness (which can be horrifying, but not <em>quite</em> in a way suitable for Halloween) than about fear, although it does address fear/s throughout the Tale - see if you can spot them all!</p> <p>(Oh, yeah, and redundant title is redundant, but fitting for Kit.)</p> <p>Thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/leveritas" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1558990&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1509287750" alt="Leveritas" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1558990)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/leveritas" >Leveritas</a></span> for spurring me on as always.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
